yYdsdZIcNnA1pMPR-uAnW49xzoQGkPklhfQbKZfNefJxBm9hP2vD74t_f_gkO6KTYg3H6RDU-SW0HZyDovic5LyJTOk4VXOpWDszl5yk3n4_GWyXW6QL4p0G_orhiWTWFKahpmeaTJoBulCKv-qtzqhG-9gKqhiq4rxa9MYRJ5XcwwoHn06ShhgjUE8tq-f722_RHKQDBzzWVWTyWdeSa3w2kZ_MqR-8nMKekRPcIx33SAzuuHR_Kcb2ze37xHS9x08gDmpjt1kUMBf_NKtD6fIAROFQ-dAKqsHzrWmKvBAAAb00Xhpl3nyvOPGTu7HC-5sQKahWGC1kNsV7kKVNtGb2Yltq5fuRysiQC3hb_WeQajmqirpocDPKeDpFExBRfR9MoqHKMdnev9oqnCh45H4JcWBj9_vSCmX08rItiN1LKeecZVpNi15S4V2jKdJXEwOziGS-RKXkjU55wCDYzvBKu5JKqofss4B2ggv3p3J7tHdb-i4Fgrr9q-O02W4i1lw5P-XK4NtgoSgBmM5bCUyGXe1tTs4n8VayZ3Z0Ef1vHKgKeOEKeVmRPnjG7OfZ\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing serialization features**\\n\\nI’m looking at the serialization features from the configuration, and it seems like the setting WRITE_DATES_AS_TIMESTAMPS is currently off. It's worth noting that a custom factory can be set up through bootstrap, which can change the mapper features. There's also a more advanced public API related to the JacksonObjectMapperProviderSetup that could be useful. I need to remember this as it can impact how I handle date serialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class names**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to map old class names. It seems like the currentVersion might apply only to the specific class if its key class name is \\\"New.\\\" This makes me wonder about how effectively I can use these mappings. Do I need to consider edge cases or other scenarios too? It feels like a detail that could be really important later on, so I want to be careful with how I handle it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating actor reference resolution**\\n\\nI’m looking into deserialized dead letters, which might be linked to the actor path string \\\"akka://System/deadLetters.\\\" It seems like using resolveActorRef can return dead letters, which is good. Now I need to focus on Address serialization directly in JsonPayload. I'll also consider how to implement a public API for the ActorRef resolver. This seems like a critical aspect to get right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EffMVrFgFtI9rltRAtZV2M3v|fc_0b70f9f7ffa7ea7e0169fb0f056f7881958d93d3d705bc4ed1", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-serialization-jackson_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_serialization_jackson_2_13/Akka_serialization_jackson_2_13Test.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_akka.akka_serialization_jackson_2_13\n\nimport akka.actor.ActorRef\nimport akka.actor.ActorSystem\nimport akka.actor.Address\nimport akka.serialization.SerializationExtension\nimport akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonMigration\nimport akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonObjectMapperProvider\nimport akka.serialization.jackson.JacksonSerializer\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode\nimport com.typesafe.config.Config\nimport com.typesafe.config.ConfigFactory\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\nimport java.time.Instant\nimport java.util.Optional\nimport scala.concurrent.Await\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.DurationInt\nimport scala.concurrent.duration.FiniteDuration\n\nclass Akka_serialization_jackson_2_13Test {\n  @Test\n  def jsonSerializerRoundTripsScalaAndAkkaTypesWithGzipCompression(): Unit = {\n    val config: Config = configWithBindings(\n      Map(classOf[JsonPayload] -> \"jackson-json\"),\n      \"\"\"\n        akka.serialization.jackson.jackson-json.compression {\n          algorithm = gzip\n          compress-larger-than = 1 byte\n        }\n        \"\"\"\n    )\n\n    withActorSystem(\"JacksonJsonRoundTrip\", config) { system =>\n      val payload: JsonPayload = JsonPayload(\n        id = \"json-1\",\n        count = 17,\n        created = Instant.parse(\"2024-05-01T10:15:30Z\"),\n        maybe = Some(\"present\"),\n        javaMaybe = Optional.of(Integer.valueOf(42)),\n        timeout = 1250.millis,\n        address = Address(\"akka\", system.name, \"127.0.0.1\", 2552),\n        description = \"payload-data-\" * 100\n      )\n\n      val serialization = SerializationExtension(system)\n      val serializer = serialization.serializerFor(classOf[JsonPayload]).asInstanceOf[JacksonSerializer]\n      val bytes: Array[Byte] = serializer.toBinary(payload)\n      val copy = serializer.fromBinary(bytes, serializer.manifest(payload)).asInstanceOf[JsonPayload]\n\n      assertThat(serializer.identifier()).isEqualTo(31)\n      assertThat(JacksonSerializer.isGZipped(bytes)).isTrue()\n      assertThat(copy).isEqualTo(payload)\n      assertThat(serialization.serialize(payload).get).isNotEmpty\n      assertThat(serialization.deserialize(bytes, classOf[JsonPayload]).get).isEqualTo(payload)\n    }\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def cborSerializerRoundTripsCompactBinaryPayloads(): Unit = {\n    val config: Config = configWithBindings(Map(classOf[CborPayload] -> \"jackson-cbor\"))\n\n    withActorSystem(\"JacksonCborRoundTrip\", config) { system =>\n      val payload: CborPayload = CborPayload(\n        id = \"cbor-1\",\n        values = Vector.range(1, 12),\n        address = Address(\"akka\", system.name, \"localhost\", 2553),\n        nested = NestedPayload(\"nested\", enabled = true)\n      )\n\n      val serialization = SerializationExtension(system)\n      val serializer = serialization.serializerFor(classOf[CborPayload]).asInstanceOf[JacksonSerializer]\n      val bytes: Array[Byte] = serializer.toBinary(payload)\n      val copy = serializer.fromBinary(bytes, serializer.manifest(payload)).asInstanceOf[CborPayload]\n\n      assertThat(serializer.identifier()).isEqualTo(33)\n      assertThat(bytes).isNotEmpty\n      assertThat(JacksonSerializer.isGZipped(bytes