[thinking] **Analyzing potential issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about potential failures relating to LZ4 in Native, particularly if the lz4-java library uses unsafe or metadata as a dependency. I want to keep things simple and not include "Cbor compact" bytes with LZ4. There are also issues with gzip assertions; `toBinary` should only compress when the length exceeds a threshold, which I’ve set to 1 byte.
[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to look into how serialized bytes interact with the deserialization process, especially with an ActorSystem that may warn if `akka.actor.allow-java-serialization` is off. There’s also the problem of migrating old manifests with uncompressed bytes; I wonder if JSON binding compression could create more complications.
